The European Bank for
Reconstruction and Development is loaning the Romanian water
utility Compania de Apa Oltenia SA funds to finance projects to
modernize and expand supply networks and wastewater services.  The EBRD said today in a statement that by co-financing a
663 million-leu ($201 million) investment program in southern
Dolj County, the utility will receive up to 57 million leu under
the Romania EU Cohesion Fundâ€™s water framework. The projects
include renovations, extensions and water and sewage treatment
works in Craiova, Calafat and Filiasi.  To contact the reporter on this story:
